\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Thinking about method invocation**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering how to invoke a method dynamically. It seems like I need the actual `Method#invoke` call to get this right. Maybe the active class should be a public bytecode that includes a public constructor. I think I could instantiate it using Java or Scala, making sure I understand the binary name. There’s a bit of complexity to navigate, but I’m curious about how it all ties together!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering dynamic class loading**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how the existing runtime compile process works; it only compiles without loading the compiled class, which might require a macro. I’m wondering if using a runtime source with a top-level val would help, but it seems that just compiling doesn't run it. Maybe I could use the Scala compiler with URLClassLoader for dynamic loading. I need to be careful with tests so that I'm not placing them in the same package, and I guess reflection might still be part of loading the generated class.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Refining test object structure**\\\\n\\\\nThe existing class file isn't active, so I should create private helpers in a new test object. I’ll include a dedicated file for these helpers, and I don't need to run the tests for now. I need to ensure that all imports and syntax are correct. The package should match the existing one. As for naming, I'll conform to the rule that indicates replacing `$` followed by a name with \\\\\\\"InnerName\\\\\\\" for the test name.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_b95Z6nV19NjJgAPEB7Unw5sL|fc_00b639cdf3529b810169fa2af479008194a54c2cd275a08be5\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala/jsoniter_scala_macros_3/CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeInnerHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTest.scala\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala.jsoniter_scala_macros_3\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport java.io.File\\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\nimport java.util.Comparator\\nimport java.util.stream.Stream\\nimport scala.collection.mutable.ArrayBuffer\\n\\nclass CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeInnerHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTest {\\n  import CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeInnerHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTest.*\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def compilesMacroThatInvokesHelperObjectReflectionMethodCall(): Unit = {\\n    try {\\n      compileMacroSupportAndUsage()\\n    } catch {\\n      case error: Error =>\\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n          throw error\\n        }\\n      case ex: InvocationTargetException if ex.getCause.isInstanceOf[Error] =>\\n        val error: Error = ex.getCause.asInstanceOf[Error]\\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n          throw error\\n        }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nobject CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeInnerHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTest {\\n  def compileMacroSupportAndUsage(): Unit = {\\n    val rootDir: Path = Files.createTempDirectory(\\\"jsoniter-helper-object-call-\\\")\\n    try {\\n      val outputDir: Path = Files.createDirectory(rootDir.resolve(\\\"classes\\\"))\\n      val supportSource: Path = rootDir.resolve(\\\"HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallMacro.scala\\\")\\n      val usageSource: Path = rootDir.resolve(\\\"HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallUsage.scala\\\")\\n\\n      Files.write(\\n        supportSource,\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n          |package com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter_scala.macros\\n          |\\n          |import scala.quoted.*\\n          |\\n          |final class HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTarget {\\n          |  def combine(owner: HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTarget, suffix: String): String =\\n          |    \\\"helper_\\\" + suffix\\n          |}\\n          |\\n          |object HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallMacro {\\n          |  inline def mappedName: String = ${ mappedNameImpl }\\n          |\\n          |  def mappedNameImpl(using Quotes): Expr[String] = {\\n          |    val scope = new CompileTimeEval.QuoteScope()\\n          |    val target = new HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallTarget()\\n          |    val call = new scope.HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCall(\\n          |      target,\\n          |      target,\\n          |      \\\"combine\\\",\\n          |      Array(\\\"value\\\".asInstanceOf[AnyRef])\\n          |    )\\n          |    Expr(call.process().asInstanceOf[String])\\n          |  }\\n          |}\\n          |\\\"\\\"\\\".stripMargin.getBytes(UTF_8)\\n      )\\n      invokeScalaCompiler(\\n        Array(\\n          \\\"-classpath\\\",\\n          runtimeClasspath,\\n          \\\"-d\\\",\\n          outputDir.toString,\\n          supportSource.toString\\n        )\\n      )\\n\\n      Files.write(\\n        usageSource,\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n          |package compiled_jsoniter_helper_object\\n          |\\n          |import com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter_scala.macros.HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallMacro\\n          |\\n          |object HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallUsage {\\n          |  val mappedName: String = HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCallMacro.mappedName\\n          |}\\n          |\\\"\\\"\\\".stripMargin.getBytes(UTF_8)\\n     