"helper_value\\\\\\\" = Helper...mappedName`. I need to ensure the macro returns a singleton type. If I define `transparent inline def mappedName: String`, maybe it can be refined. I wonder if I can simplify it further by just using `transparent inline def mappedName = ${ mappedNameImpl }` without an explicit return type, but does the macro need a return type? That’s something to consider!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Inspecting errors and processes**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about the literal singleton, but I'm feeling a bit unsure about its necessity. It seems like maybe the phase compile support doesn't actually execute the process, so there wouldn't be an error; the usage could be expanding. If call.process throws an error, then the compiler will report a macro exception and mark hasErrors as true. That's good, but I really need to inspect the status further to clarify things.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_eCwLMzagfaS0ClGsZim6xTpn|fc_00b639cdf3529b810169fa2b0a916481948794494283f202ae\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"git status --short\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 5366, \"output\": 587, \"cacheRead\": 21504, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 27457, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778002686451, \"responseId\": \"resp_00b639cdf3529b810169fa2afef5948194856d1d7159e652f3\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_eCwLMzagfaS0ClGsZim6xTpn|fc_00b639cdf3529b810169fa2b0a916481948794494283f202ae\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/\\n?? tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33